HEADWORD: Collembola
<hw>Col*lem"bo*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>ko`lla</grk> glue + <grk>'e`mbolon</grk> wedge, peg; -- so
called from their having collophores.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
division of Thysanura which includes <gen>Podura</gen>, and allied
forms.</def>⟦br⟧
